ehrten vor allem die weit verstreuten Arbeiten über seine Sprachauffassung gesammelt sind.  aThese two volumes comprising 1526 pages contain a reproduction of the original text of Schottelius' most important work, a 'Baroque summa philologica' of the German language. It is supplemented by a commentary by the editor, which describes the "Detailed Account .", outlines the history of its reception and influence, provides a brief biography of its author, a bibliography of his writings in the field of language theory, and a general bibliography of relevant literature.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aGerman languagexGrammarvEarly works to 1800. 0aGerman languagexVersification. 0aGerman languageyEarly modern, 1500-1700xGrammar. 0aProverbs, German. 4aDeutsch. 4aGeschichte 1663. 4aQuelle. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aHecht, Wolfgang, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 1990 - 1999z9783110636895oZDB-23-DLS0 cprintz978348416008840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311094046640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110940466423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110940466/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DLSc1990d1999